* =============================================================================
* tb_pcn_4layer.spice — 4-module 16×16 chip integration testbench
* Generated by gen_tb_4layer.py  — DO NOT EDIT by hand.
*
* Tests:
*   T1 (op-point):  bias rails correct; ascending path m0→m1→m2→m3 verified;
*                   descending predictions m0_pred..m2_pred non-zero; error
*                   flags HIGH at top (mod3, i_pred=VSS) and variable below.
*   T2 (DC sweep):  raw_inp_0 ±50mV; signal gain tracked layer by layer.
*   T3 (transient): Hebbian write on mod0 row 0; ΔVw > 0 confirms LTP path.
*
* Circuit hierarchy:
*   Stiff sources — vbias_n=0.760V, vcm=0.900V, vpi=0.650V, ncm_iout=0.468V
*   ncm_iout = actual balanced iout OP (NOT Vcm=0.9V which is the input CM) (§72 fix)
*   PMOS SF level shift (§71/72): V(m0_iout)≈0.468V + |Vgs_P|≈0.67V → V(m1_inp)≈1.14V
*   vcm_upper per link: ref PMOS SF output ≈ ncm_iout + |Vgs_P| ≈ 1.14V (§72 fix)
*   vcm_upper_01/12/23 are driven by the reference SFs inside each layer_link_16.
*   Xmod0..Xmod3     — pcn_module_16x16 (array + current_sub + precision_gate)
*   Xlink_01..23     — layer_link_16 (ascending PMOS SF + descending XMPRED)
* =============================================================================

.title PCN 4-Layer 16×16 Chip Integration Testbench

.lib "$PDK_ROOT/sky130A/libs.tech/ngspice/sky130.lib.spice" tt
.include "pcn_mac_cell.spice"
.include "pcn_array_16x16.spice"
.include "pcn_module_16x16.spice"
.include "layer_link.spice"

* ── Simulation options ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.options RELTOL=1e-3 ABSTOL=1e-12 VNTOL=1e-6 GMIN=1e-10 ITL1=300 ITL4=100

* ── Supplies ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Vvdd  vdd  0  DC 1.8
Vvss  vss  0  DC 0

* ── Stiff bias rails ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
* vcm_upper_01/12/23: driven by reference SFs inside each layer_link_16 (§71).
* ncm_iout: stiff 0.468V — actual balanced iout OP (measured); drives reference SF
*           gate so vcm_upper tracks actual iout CM, not input Vcm (§72 fix).
Vbias_n    vbias_n    0  DC 0.760
Vcm_src    vcm        0  DC 0.900
Vpi_src    vpi        0  DC 0.650
Vcm_iout   ncm_iout   0  DC 0.468

* ── nc_vbias_p: floating port in all modules — tie weakly to VDD ───────────
Rnc  nc_vbias_p  vdd  1000meg

* ── Module 0 column inputs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
Vinp0  raw_inp_0  0  DC 0.9
